@pipeline @smoke
Feature: Grocery Intelligence Pipeline # features/pipeline.feature:2
  As a data engineer
  I want a medallion pipeline that ingests ABS retail and CPI data
  So that gold tables are ready for the workshop demo app
  @pipeline @smoke
  Feature: Grocery Intelligence Pipeline  # features/pipeline.feature:2

  Scenario: Bronze retail table has data from ABS                                # features/pipeline.feature:12
    Given a connection to the Databricks workspace                               # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:40
    And the catalog "workshop_vibe_coding" exists                                # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:46
    And the schema "demo" exists                                                 # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:52
    When I query "workshop_vibe_coding.demo.bronze_abs_retail_trade"             # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:62
    Then the table should have more than 8000 rows                               # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:76
    And the table should have columns "REGION, INDUSTRY, TIME_PERIOD, OBS_VALUE" # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:82

  Scenario: Bronze CPI table has data from ABS                                # features/pipeline.feature:17
    Given a connection to the Databricks workspace                            # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:40
    And the catalog "workshop_vibe_coding" exists                             # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:46
    And the schema "demo" exists                                              # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:52
    When I query "workshop_vibe_coding.demo.bronze_abs_cpi_food"              # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:62
    Then the table should have more than 400 rows                             # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:76
    And the table should have columns "REGION, INDEX, TIME_PERIOD, OBS_VALUE" # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:82

  Scenario: Silver retail turnover has decoded states               # features/pipeline.feature:22
    Given a connection to the Databricks workspace                  # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:40
    And the catalog "workshop_vibe_coding" exists                   # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:46
    And the schema "demo" exists                                    # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:52
    When I query "workshop_vibe_coding.demo.silver_retail_turnover" # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:62
    Then the table should have more than 7000 rows                  # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:76
    And the column "state" should contain "New South Wales"         # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:91
    And the column "state" should not contain "1"                   # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:98
    And there should be 8 distinct values in "state"                # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:105

  Scenario: Silver retail turnover has no nulls                     # features/pipeline.feature:29
    Given a connection to the Databricks workspace                  # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:40
    And the catalog "workshop_vibe_coding" exists                   # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:46
    And the schema "demo" exists                                    # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:52
    When I query "workshop_vibe_coding.demo.silver_retail_turnover" # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:62
    Then the column "date" should have zero nulls                   # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:112
    And the column "turnover_millions" should have zero nulls       # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:112
    And all values in "turnover_millions" should be greater than 0  # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:119

  Scenario: Silver food price index has quarterly dates              # features/pipeline.feature:35
    Given a connection to the Databricks workspace                   # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:40
    And the catalog "workshop_vibe_coding" exists                    # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:46
    And the schema "demo" exists                                     # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:52
    When I query "workshop_vibe_coding.demo.silver_food_price_index" # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:62
    Then the table should have more than 400 rows                    # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:76
    And the column "state" should contain "Victoria"                 # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:91
    And the column "cpi_index" should have zero nulls                # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:112

  Scenario: Gold retail summary has rolling averages and YoY growth                                                    # features/pipeline.feature:41
    Given a connection to the Databricks workspace                                                                     # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:40
    And the catalog "workshop_vibe_coding" exists                                                                      # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:46
    And the schema "demo" exists                                                                                       # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:52
    When I query "workshop_vibe_coding.demo.gold_retail_summary"                                                       # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:62
    Then the table should have more than 1000 rows                                                                     # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:76
    And the table should have columns "state, date, total_turnover, turnover_3m_avg, turnover_12m_avg, yoy_growth_pct" # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:82
    And there should be 8 distinct values in "state"                                                                   # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:105
    And the column "turnover_3m_avg" should have zero nulls                                                            # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:112

  Scenario: Gold retail summary date range spans 2010 to 2025      # features/pipeline.feature:48
    Given a connection to the Databricks workspace                 # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:40
    And the catalog "workshop_vibe_coding" exists                  # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:46
    And the schema "demo" exists                                   # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:52
    When I query "workshop_vibe_coding.demo.gold_retail_summary"   # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:62
    Then the minimum value in "date" should be before "2010-06-01" # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:136
    And the maximum value in "date" should be after "2025-01-01"   # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:143

  Scenario: Gold food inflation has YoY change percentages                     # features/pipeline.feature:53
    Given a connection to the Databricks workspace                             # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:40
    And the catalog "workshop_vibe_coding" exists                              # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:46
    And the schema "demo" exists                                               # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:52
    When I query "workshop_vibe_coding.demo.gold_food_inflation_yoy"           # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:62
    Then the table should have more than 400 rows                              # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:76
    And the table should have columns "state, date, cpi_index, yoy_change_pct" # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:82
    And all values in "yoy_change_pct" should be between -50 and 100           # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:126

  Scenario: NSW has the highest total retail turnover                                                                                                         # features/pipeline.feature:59
    Given a connection to the Databricks workspace                                                                                                            # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:40
    And the catalog "workshop_vibe_coding" exists                                                                                                             # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:46
    And the schema "demo" exists                                                                                                                              # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:52
    When I run SQL "SELECT state, SUM(total_turnover) as total FROM workshop_vibe_coding.demo.gold_retail_summary GROUP BY state ORDER BY total DESC LIMIT 1" # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:67
    Then the first row "state" should be "New South Wales"                                                                                                    # features/steps/pipeline_steps.py:150

